export const PUBLIC_SECURITY_MD: string = `# 🔐 Security at Mother Brain

> How Mother Brain protects your data, your privacy, and your AI's memory.

---

## Our Security Philosophy

Mother Brain is built on a **local-first, zero-trust** security model. Your data stays on your machine by default. When cloud features are used, every request is authenticated, every project is isolated, and every action is scoped to authorized access only.

We don't just follow security best practices — we architect security into every layer of the platform.

---

## Local-First Privacy

**Your data never leaves your machine unless you explicitly choose to sync it.**

Mother Brain bundles PostgreSQL with pgvector directly inside the application. Your projects, memories, chat histories, and indexed content all live locally — on your hardware, under your control.

- **No forced cloud sync** — Local storage is the default
- **No telemetry** — We don't track usage patterns or send analytics
- **No data harvesting** — Your AI's memory belongs to you

When you enable optional cloud sync via Supabase, only the data you choose to sync leaves your device, and it's protected by Row Level Security in PostgreSQL.

---

## Per-Project Isolation

Every project in Mother Brain is **fully isolated** from every other project.

- Each project gets its own PostgreSQL instance with independent RBAC (Role-Based Access Control)
- **Zero cross-contamination** — A user or AI agent working in Project A cannot access any data from Project B
- The **AI Router** enforces project boundaries at the gateway level — every message and every tool call is validated against the authenticated project scope before any data is accessed

This means your work projects, personal projects, and client projects are always separate. Always.

---

## Authentication & Access Control

Mother Brain uses a layered credential system:

### Master API Key
- Provides full platform access for the project owner
- Required for administrative operations and project management
- Stored securely and never exposed in client-side code

### Project API Keys
- One key per project, used to route external app messages to the correct project
- Ensures that your Zed IDE, Obsidian, Cursor, or custom app connects only to the project you intend
- Keys are project-scoped — a compromised project key cannot access other projects

### User Access Tokens
- Short-lived, per-session tokens for individual users
- Validated on the server side — the client is never trusted directly
- Tokens expire automatically and must be refreshed

### What This Means for You
- **No single point of failure** — Multiple credential layers mean a compromised token doesn't compromise the platform
- **Server-side validation** — Authentication decisions happen on secure infrastructure, not on your device where they could be tampered with
- **License enforcement happens server-side** — Subscription and licensing checks are performed against verified backend services

---

## Cloud Infrastructure Security

Mother Brain's cloud components are deployed on **Cloudflare's global edge network**:

- **Cloudflare Workers** — Mother's A2A Agent runs on Cloudflare's edge, benefiting from Cloudflare's DDoS protection, WAF (Web Application Firewall), and Bot Management
- **Cloudflare Tunnel** — Secure remote access to your Mother Brain instance from any device, without exposing ports or IP addresses
- **SSL/TLS everywhere** — All connections are encrypted in transit
- **Cloudflare API Shield** — API endpoints are protected by rate limiting, schema validation, and threat intelligence

### Supabase (Auth & Optional Sync)
- Industry-standard authentication powered by Supabase
- Row Level Security (RLS) in PostgreSQL ensures users can only access their own data
- Data encrypted at rest and in transit
- Used only for optional cloud sync and subscription management — not required for local-only use

---

## Data Protection

### At Rest
- Local data is stored in PostgreSQL on your machine
- Sensitive credentials are stored using platform-level secure key storage (e.g., macOS Keychain)
- Encrypted storage for sensitive local data when needed

### In Transit
- All API communications use HTTPS with TLS encryption
- Cloudflare Tunnel encrypts all traffic between your device and the cloud
- WebSocket connections for streaming are also TLS-encrypted

### AI Agent Security
- Mother (the A2A Agent) operates with **context-aware authorization** — every action is evaluated based on identity, project scope, and data classification
- Mother **never shares** other users' data, conversations, or personal information
- Mother **never reveals** internal implementation details, codebase information, or security architecture specifics
- Prompt-level data controls prevent sensitive information from appearing in AI responses

---

## A2A Protocol Security

Mother communicates via the **A2A (Agent-to-Agent) protocol** using JSON-RPC 2.0:

- **Authenticated connections** — External agents must authenticate before interaction
- **Session isolation** — Each session is independent with unique identifiers
- **Scoped access** — Agents can only access data within their authenticated project scope
- **No cross-project data leakage** — The AI Router enforces boundaries at every request

---

## Security Monitoring

- Cloudflare Security dashboards provide real-time monitoring of edge traffic and threats
- Anomalous patterns, unauthorized access attempts, and suspicious behavior are logged for review
- Security telemetry is aggregated and monitored to prioritize remediation

---

## Responsible Disclosure

If you discover a security vulnerability in Mother Brain, we want to hear from you.

**How to report:** Chat with **Mother** — directly on [motherbrain.app](https://motherbrain.app) or inside the Mother Brain app's Support Chat. She's available instantly, 24/7.

We ask that you:
1. Report the vulnerability responsibly — do not publicly disclose before we've had a chance to respond
2. Provide enough detail for us to reproduce and verify the issue
3. Allow reasonable time for a fix before public disclosure

We commit to:
1. Acknowledging your report within 48 hours
2. Keeping you updated on our progress
3. Crediting you in our security acknowledgments (with your permission)

**If Mother doesn't have the answer**, she'll escalate to our development team directly. We'll update her knowledge base and the website so the answer is there for the next person who asks.

---

## Summary

| Layer | Protection |
|---|---|
| **Data Storage** | Local-first, PostgreSQL on your machine, encrypted at rest |
| **Project Isolation** | Per-project instances, RBAC, zero cross-contamination |
| **Authentication** | Master API Key + Project API Keys + User Access Tokens |
| **Transport** | TLS/SSL everywhere, Cloudflare Tunnel for remote access |
| **Edge Security** | Cloudflare WAF, DDoS protection, Bot Management, API Shield |
| **AI Agent** | Context-aware authorization, scoped access, session isolation |
| **Cloud Sync** | Optional, Supabase with Row Level Security, encrypted |
| **Privacy** | No forced telemetry, no data harvesting, local-first by default |

---

*Security is not a feature we add — it's the foundation we build on. Mother Brain is designed so that your AI's memory is powerful, persistent, and private.*`;

